Tested metabolites (usnic acid and/or arabitol) were added to a starch gel at the mean concentrations found in the thalli. The feeding experiment lasted 48 h. Gel-mixed metabolites had a significant impact on their consumption by snails (Chi 
2
= 57.47, df = 3, P <0.001; 
Fig. 7
). Snails offered gels with usnic acid alone mainly avoided it (Tukey, P <0.001). Gels supplemented with arabitol were eaten as much as the starch control alone (Tukey, P = 0.795; 
Fig. 7
). Gels containing a mixture of arabitol and usnic acid were consumed more than usnic acid gels alone (Tukey, P <0.001), but less than arabitol gels alone (Tukey, P = 0.009).
